10 4–217.
11 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
12 INDICATED.
13 (2) “DISTRICT COUNCIL” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 14–101 OF
14 THIS ARTICLE “CENTRAL NATURAL AREA” MEANS AN AREA WITHIN THE PATUXENT
15 RESEARCH REFUGE OR THE BELTSVILLE AGRICULTURAL RESEARCH CENTER
16 THAT PROVIDES HABITAT FOR NATIVE FLORA AND FAUNA, INCLUDING FORESTS,
17 WOODLANDS, WETLANDS, MEADOWS, AND EARLY SUCCESSIONAL GRASSLANDS AND
18 SHRUBLANDS.
19 (3) “LOCAL ZONING AUTHORITY” MEANS:
20 (I) A LOCAL JURISDICTION FOR LAND LOCATED IN ANNE
21 ARUNDEL COUNTY, THE ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY COUNCIL OR OTHER BODY WITH
22 AUTHORITY TO DESIGNATE ZONING CLASSIFICATIONS; OR
23 (II) FOR PROPERTY LAND LOCATED IN THE
24 MARYLAND–WASHINGTON REGIONAL DISTRICT ESTABLISHED UNDER TITLE 20,
25 SUBTITLE 1 OF THIS ARTICLE, A DISTRICT COUNCIL, AS DEFINED IN § 14–101 OF
26 THIS ARTICLE.
27 (B) ANY FEDERALLY OWNED LAND THAT IS PART OF THE PROPERTY KNOWN
28 AS THE PATUXENT RESEARCH REFUGE SHALL BE DESIGNATED AND MAINTAINED IN
29 A ZONING CLASSIFICATION THAT RESTRICTS THE USES TO OPEN SPACE, RESERVED
30 OPEN SPACE, OR OTHER RESOURCE CONSERVATION USES.

4 HOUSE BILL 1267
1 (C) IF THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT OR ANY ASSIGNEE SELLS, LEASES,
2 LICENSES, OR OTHERWISE ENCUMBERS ANY PORTION OF LAND THAT IS PART OF THE
3 PROPERTY KNOWN AS THE PATUXENT RESEARCH REFUGE, THE LOCAL ZONING
4 AUTHORITY SHALL CONTINUE A ZONING CLASSIFICATION FOR THAT PROPERTY
5 THAT:
6 (1) RESTRICTS THE USES TO OPEN SPACE, RESERVED OPEN SPACE,
7 OR OTHER RESOURCE CONSERVATION USES; AND
8 (2) DOES NOT PERMIT COMMERCIAL, INDUSTRIAL, OR RESIDENTIAL
9 USES.
10 (D) A CENTRAL NATURAL AREA IN THE PROPERTY KNOWN AS THE
11 PATUXENT RESEARCH REFUGE MAY NOT BE CONVERTED TO BE USED FOR
12 AGRICULTURE, ACTIVE RECREATION, FORESTRY, OR OTHER PLANT HARVESTING.
13 (E) PRIOR TO ANY DEVELOPMENT ON LAND IN THE PROPERTY KNOWN AS
14 THE PATUXENT RESEARCH REFUGE, THE LOCAL ZONING AUTHORITY SHALL:
15 (1) HOLD A PUBLIC HEARING; AND
16 (2) MAKE A FINAL DECISION, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE
17 MARYLAND DEPARTMENT OF NATURAL RESOURCES AND THE MARYLAND
18 DEPARTMENT OF THE ENVIRONMENT, THAT THE PROPOSED DEVELOPMENT WILL
19 NOT HAVE A SUBSTANTIAL IMPACT ON ANY LAND IN A CENTRAL NATURAL AREA.
20 [25–211.
21 If the United States Department of Agriculture sells any portion of the property
22 known as the Beltsville Agricultural Research Center, the district council shall place and
23 permanently maintain the land in a zoning classification of agricultural open space
24 immediately after the transfer of the land to the buyer.]
25 25–211.
26 (A) SUBJECT TO SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, THE THE DISTRICT
27 COUNCIL SHALL DESIGNATE AND MAINTAIN THE FEDERALLY OWNED PROPERTY
28 KNOWN AS THE BELTSVILLE AGRICULTURAL RESEARCH CENTER OR ANY OTHER
29 U.S. DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE PROPERTY IN BELTSVILLE OR ITS VICINITY
30 TO A ZONING CLASSIFICATION THAT RESTRICTS THE USES TO OPEN SPACE OR
31 RESERVED OPEN SPACE.
32 (B) IF THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT OR ANY ASSIGNEE SELLS, LEASES,
33 LICENSES, OR OTHERWISE ENCUMBERS ANY PORTION OF THE PROPERTY KNOWN AS

HOUSE BILL 1267 5
1 THE BELTSVILLE AGRICULTURAL RESEARCH CENTER OR ANY OTHER U.S.
2 DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE PROPERTY IN BELTSVILLE OR ITS VICINITY, THE
3 DISTRICT COUNCIL SHALL CONTINUE A ZONING CLASSIFICATION FOR THAT
4 PROPERTY THAT:
5 (1) RESTRICTS THE USES TO OPEN SPACE OR RESERVED OPEN SPACE;
6 AND
7 (2) DOES NOT PERMIT COMMERCIAL, INDUSTRIAL, OR RESIDENTIAL
8 USES.
9 (C) THE DISTRICT COUNCIL MAY NOT APPROVE ANY OVERLAYS, SPECIAL
10 EXCEPTIONS, OR MODIFICATIONS TO THE ZONING CLASSIFICATIONS REQUIRED BY
11 THIS SECTION.
12 (C) A CENTRAL NATURAL AREA, AS DEFINED IN § 4–217 OF THIS ARTICLE,
13 IN THE PROPERTY KNOWN AS THE BELTSVILLE AGRICULTURAL RESEARCH CENTER
14 MAY NOT BE CONVERTED TO BE USED FOR AGRICULTURE, ACTIVE RECREATION,
15 FORESTRY, OR OTHER PLANT HARVESTING.
16 (D) PRIOR TO ANY DEVELOPMENT ON LAND IN THE PROPERTY KNOWN AS
17 THE BELTSVILLE AGRICULTURAL RESEARCH CENTER, THE DISTRICT COUNCIL
18 SHALL:
19 (1) HOLD A PUBLIC HEARING; AND
20 (2) MAKE A FINAL DECISION, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE
21 MARYLAND DEPARTMENT OF NATURAL RESOURCES AND THE MARYLAND
22 DEPARTMENT OF THE ENVIRONMENT, THAT THE PROPOSED DEVELOPMENT WILL
23 NOT HAVE A SUBSTANTIAL IMPACT ON ANY LAND IN A CENTRAL NATURAL AREA.
24 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
25 1, 2026.

